                            <comment id="12882771" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2010 23:50:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Linking to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2223&quot; title=&quot;Handle 10min+ network partitions between clusters&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2223&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2223&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which heavily uses ZK.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12882812" author="tlipcon" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2010 05:18:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree, warning and continuing is almost always the wrong thing to do.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Last weekend I took an hour or so and prototyped some wrapper APIs here:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://github.com/toddlipcon/hbase/blob/zk-cleanup/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/zookeeper/ZKAction.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://github.com/toddlipcon/hbase/blob/zk-cleanup/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/zookeeper/ZKAction.java&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These APIs let you do stuff like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
ZKAction.create(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/foo&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).doOrThrowRTE() vs
ZKAction.create(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/foo&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).withWatcher(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;).onExceptionReturn(KeeperException.Foo.class, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;).doOrThrowIOE()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having convenient shorthand to &quot;do the right thing&quot; will probably discourage people from the lazy IDE autocomplete exception ignoring that we often do.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12902220" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 25 Aug 2010 00:44:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is all redone in the master rewrite.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12998985" author="nilsk" created="Thu, 24 Feb 2011 18:36:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You should throw the InterruptedExceptions instead of swallowing it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just picked a sample from here &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/hbase/trunk/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/zookeeper/ZooKeeperWatcher.java?view=markup&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;ZooKeeperWatcher&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  /**
   * Close the connection to ZooKeeper.
   * @&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; InterruptedException
   */
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void close() {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (zooKeeper != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
        zooKeeper.close();
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;super&lt;/span&gt;.close();
&lt;/span&gt;      }
    } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (InterruptedException e) {
    }
  }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thats the worst thing you could do with an InterruptedException. Please see &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/java/library/j-jtp05236.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;this&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017071" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:41:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
